
Dan Shamash
instance
Dan Shamash a.k.a. Smash (born December 20, 1985 in New York City) is an American football coach for the Jacksonville Jaguars of the National Football League (NFL), following stints with the Tampa Bay Buccaneers and Cleveland Browns. Shamash joined the Browns after serving in the game operations and special events department for the New York Jets in 2008, spending time as a defensive assistant for Columbia University. A graduate of Carnegie Mellon University, Shamash was a 3-year letter winner at inside linebacker. Shamash is a native of New York City. Dan Shamash is currently an assistant coach with the Tampa Bay Buccaneers.